21/* This file holds definitions specific to the MN10300 ELF ABI. */
22
23#ifndef _ELF_MN10300_H
24#define _ELF_MN10300_H
25
26#include "elf/reloc-macros.h"
27
28/* Relocations. */
29START_RELOC_NUMBERS (elf_mn10300_reloc_type)
30 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_NONE, 0)
31 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_32, 1)
32 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_16, 2)
33 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_8, 3)
34 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_PCREL32, 4)
35 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_PCREL16, 5)
36 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_PCREL8, 6)
37 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_GNU_VTINHERIT, 7)
38 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_GNU_VTENTRY, 8)
39 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_24, 9)
40 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_GOTPC32, 10)
41 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_GOTPC16, 11)
42 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_GOTOFF32, 12)
43 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_GOTOFF24, 13)
44 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_GOTOFF16, 14)
45 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_PLT32, 15)
46 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_PLT16, 16)
47 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_GOT32, 17)
48 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_GOT24, 18)
49 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_GOT16, 19)
50 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_COPY, 20)
51 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MN10300_GLOB_DAT, 21)

65END_RELOC_NUMBERS (R_MN10300_MAX)
66
67/* Machine variant if we know it. This field was invented at Cygnus,
68 but it is hoped that other vendors will adopt it. If some standard
69 is developed, this code should be changed to follow it. */
70
71#define EF_MN10300_MACH 0x00FF0000
72
73/* Cygnus is choosing values between 80 and 9F;
74 00 - 7F should be left for a future standard;
75 the rest are open. */
76
77#define E_MN10300_MACH_MN10300 0x00810000
78#define E_MN10300_MACH_AM33 0x00820000
79#define E_MN10300_MACH_AM33_2 0x00830000
80#endif /* _ELF_MN10300_H */
